(4169, 250, 'accordion_section_0_accordion_content', 'Ideally fencing should be built along the outer edge of the grassy strip or at the very least, along riparian edge or setback. This allows the filtration services provided by the buffer to continue. In some cases temporary fencing may be required especially in areas where spring flooding or ice may damage the fences.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://projects.cs.dal.ca/farming/project/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Riparian-Fencing.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-274 size-large" src="http://projects.cs.dal.ca/farming/project/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Riparian-Fencing-1024x443.png" alt="Riparian Fencing" width="474" height="205" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
