(20559, 567, '_accordion_section_1_accordion_color', 'field_5397901e00c44'),
(20560, 567, 'accordion_section_1_accordion_content', '<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Is dead plant material or litter from previous years absent?</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Is the buffer strip between the riparian zone and cultivated lands narrow (less than 10 meters)?</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Is plant vigour poor?</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Has grazing removed almost all of the palatable vegetation?</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Are desirable plants being replaced by unpalatable or undesirable types?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIs woody vegetation present and maintaining itself? Preferred trees and shrubs are established and regenerating (see list of appropriate trees and shrubs)\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Are noxious weeds present?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWeeds and grasses have shallower roots than woody species, and are therefore not as capable of controlling erosion.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Are there disturbed ground species present such as queen Annes Lace, colts foot, plantain?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[caption id="attachment_566" align="alignright" width="225"]<a href="http://projects.cs.dal.ca/farming/project/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/plantain.jpg"><img class="wp-image-566 size-medium" src="http://projects.cs.dal.ca/farming/project/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/plantain-225x300.jpg" alt="plantain" width="225" height="300" /></a> Plantains are found in disturbed areas, such as road sides and paths[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Are wetland species being replaced by drought tolerant upland species?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Do palatable trees and shrubs appear to be heavily browsed by livestock?</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Are all the trees old and/or of poor health (as opposed to being various sizes and ages)?</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Do stands of trees have an open, park-like appearance?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIt is good to have a diversity of species, including shrub species. Grasses are not as adept at maintaining bank structure and increases the riparian areas risk to erosion\r\n\r\n<strong> Have trees and shrubs been eliminated from sites (where they should be present)?</strong>'),
