(263, 1, '2014-06-17 14:00:35', '2014-06-17 14:00:35', '<i><b>Leaving Setbacks</b></i>\r\n\r\nDepending on your goals, the amount of space dedicated to a setback will vary. The wider the setback, the more benefits are provided to both the riparian and aquatic ecosystems. The width will be dependent on your own personal goals; are you interested in improving habitat? Reducing sediment or nutrients in run-off? Improving bank stability?\r\n\r\nThe following table provides a list of the benefits that result from different buffer widths.\r\n<table width="290" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7"><colgroup> <col width="162" /> <col width="97" /> </colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td width="162" height="3"><b>Function</b></td>\r\n<td width="97"><b>Width</b></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td width="162" height="3">Bank Stability</td>\r\n<td width="97">5+ meters</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td width="162" height="4">Sediment Removal</td>\r\n<td width="97">10-30 meters</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td width="162" height="4">Soil-Bound Nutrients</td>\r\n<td width="97">10-30 meters</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td width="162" height="4">Soluble Nutrients</td>\r\n<td width="97">15-50 meters</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td width="162" height="4">Aquatic Habitat</td>\r\n<td width="97">15-30 meters</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign="top">\r\n<td width="162" height="3">Terrestrial wildlife habitat</td>\r\n<td width="97">10-300 meters</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n(Harris, n.d.)', 'Setbacks', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'setbacks', '', '', '2014-07-08 20:45:08', '2014-07-08 20:45:08', '', 240, 'http://projects.cs.dal.ca/farming/project/?page_id=263', 0, 'page', '', 0),
