(494, 4, '2014-07-10 19:33:24', '2014-07-10 19:33:24', '<i><b>Reducing or limiting access to riparian areas from livestock</b></i>\r\n\r\nLivestock trample riparian areas, this reduces the function of riparian vegetation resulting in increased susceptibility to erosion and flooding, and reduced water quality. Furthermore, the feces and urine from livestock will have a direct impact on water quality.\r\n\r\nThere are different ways that you can limit the number of livestock that enter your watercourses. Depending on what your goals are (simply improving water quality, or improving water quality and terrestrial habitat) the way that these different activities are carried out may vary.', 'Limiting Livestock Access to Waterways ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '250-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-10 19:33:24', '2014-07-10 19:33:24', '', 250, 'http://projects.cs.dal.ca/farming/project/?p=494', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(496, 4, '2014-07-10 19:43:23', '2014-07-10 19:43:23', 'Riparian zones refer to the area that is next to water. The vegetation in healthy riparian zones plays an important role in maintaining the water quality. This provides many benefits for biodiversity (terrestrial species and neighbouring aquatic species), but there are, however, benefits for humans as well:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Improved water quality</strong> for recreational purposes, drinking water in wells and for livestock.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Water absorption and storage</strong>  maintains water levels in wells, and prevents flooding</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Flood control</strong>  plants on the banks reduce the speed of moving water during storm events, resulting in decreased severity of flooding</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Protecting streambanks</strong>  prevents eroded soil from entering water</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Shade</strong>  helps to reduce water temperature, and increase habitat for species such as salmon, which are of interest to anglers.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Carbon sequestration</strong>  plants act as a carbon sink</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Shelterbelt</strong>  shrubs and trees act as a windbreak, reducing wind damage</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Riparian Area', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '184-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-10 19:43:23', '2014-07-10 19:43:23', '', 184, 'http://projects.cs.dal.ca/farming/project/?p=496', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
