(553, 4, '2014-07-14 16:34:20', '2014-07-14 16:34:20', 'There are many different kinds of wetlands. Broadly defined, a wetland is an area where the water table is close to the soil surface, resulting in a place that is saturated most, if not all, of the year. Wetlands are rich in biodiversity, and also provide benefits to humans through natural processes, such as the filtration of water.', 'Wetlands', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'wetlands', '', '', '2014-07-14 16:34:20', '2014-07-14 16:34:20', '', 2, 'http://projects.cs.dal.ca/farming/project/?page_id=553', 0, 'page', '', 0),
